&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job purpose:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Procurement Coordinator is responsible for leading and managing all procurement operations for the Syria programme, ensuring timely, transparent, competitive and compliant procurement in line with GOAL’s Procurement Manual and donor requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role holds full operational ownership of procurement activities, supplier engagement, documentation quality, and team management. In parallel, the Procurement Coordinator works in technical coordination with the Supply Chain Advisor on strategic, system-level and capacity-building initiatives, including SOP updates, process improvements and system transitions. The role is expected to provide strategic oversight and operational leadership for high-value procurement, contributing to organisation-wide tender pipeline planning, spend-driven procurement strategies, and system-level improvements, while strengthening compliance, value for money, digitalisation and procurement team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NOTE&lt;/strong&gt;: This position may require travel to Saraqeb 2–3 days per week. A shuttle service between Aleppo and Saraqeb will be provided by GOAL.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duties, objectives and competencies:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Procurement Management:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure that all procurement procedures are effectively followed in compliance with the GOAL Procurement Manual and relevant donor requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and manage procurement staff, distributing tasks based on functional areas, monitoring performance and ensuring continuous on-the-job capacity development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor the progress of all procurement actions and proactively follow up on approvals to increase on-time completion of Purchase Requests and avoid delays in the system.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review, verify and approve procurement documentation prepared by procurement staff prior to submission or award&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the set up and maintenance of all procurement filing, electronic and hardcopy, and ensure that files are complete, correct and include all relevant documentation to meet audit requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide senior oversight of procurement data accuracy and visibility within the Order Tracking System (OTS) and relevant platforms, proactively monitoring lead times, identifying risks and delays, and coordinating mitigation actions with budget holders and key stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review and analyse procurement performance reports generated through the digital OTS to support achievement of strategic procurement objectives, including Value for Money, on-time delivery, and increased utilisation of Framework Agreements (FWAs).&lt;/li&gt;
